Your problems occur because of a restriction (cq bug) in the recurse function as presented in 
the other answer. 

When you load your sample YAML both &quot;nodes&quot; for the values 42 have the same id. This is a Python
optimization, and it applies to booleans, a subset of the integers (up to 100 IIRC), etc.
Since `recurse` tests for identity (using `is`), the `if v is ref` matches two times. 

This is essentially because of the object `obj` being passed in, and
